Package com.paulgreenlee.fn

Class ImListImpl<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paulgreenlee.fn.ImListImpl<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements in the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImList<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>
    public class ImListImpl<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ImList<E>, java.util.List<E>

    A simple implementation of ImList that uses a Stream supplier function to store elements.

    Along with ImList this class also implements List. The intention is that you would code against the ImList interface and ignore the extra methods defined here. However, by also implementing the standard List interface, it allows this class to be recognized as a List at runtime. This should improve interoperability with existing code and libraries.
